  "chunk_index": 32,
  "summary": "While watching golf, Lord Kettlemere discusses the game with Bunty and Eileen Bündel, mentioning that his secretary, Mr. Bettman, believes golf relies on the strength of the left arm. During this time, Bündel receives a phone call from Jimmy Sycamore. Jimmy reveals he is spending the weekend at the Cutt house and asks Bündel if she knows how to obtain a universal key. He mentions he might ask Stevens for help, noting a previous interest in a blued barrel automatic pistol. Jimmy expresses concern about a \"chimpanzee\" who sneaks around and proposes a plan to Bündel and Loire to have their car break down near Lashbury between 12:15 and 12:30 to facilitate a lunch meeting. He also notes that Terence O'Rourke is attending, whom Jimmy suspects is involved with a secret organization and the Countess. Jimmy instructs Bündel and Loire to keep both the \"gorilla\" and O'Rourke occupied until lunchtime.\n\nLater, at Lesperon, Jimmy receives a warm welcome from Countess Kürt, though Sir Oswald appears displeased. O'Rourke attempts to confuse the guests with tall tales regarding a robbery at the Draconic Church involving masked men and Russian jewels. During the gathering, Mr. Bettman observes that O'Rourke deals cards with his left hand. After dinner, while the others play bridge, Jimmy slips into Sir Oswald's study. Using a wire to open locked drawers, he searches for information regarding Mr. Hel Eberhard's invention or the mysterious \"seven o'clock,\" but he finds nothing of interest.",
